<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Coast Guard Rescues Five People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PETIT BOIS ISLAND, Miss. (AP) -- A Coast Guard helicopter crew  
looking for a sunken barge rescued a 7-year-old boy, four adults 
and three golden retrievers from two boats awash near a Mississippi 
island. 
</P>
<P>
	The boy and two adults suffered from subnormal body  
temperatures. All five people were to be taken to a hospital for 
evaluation. 
</P>
<P>
	``At one point we had five survivors and three big dogs in our  
helicopter. It was crowded, but it was a neat rescue,'' said Lt. 
Tim Grimes. 
</P>
<P>
	He and his crew were looking for a rock barge which broke loose  
from a tow and sank early Sunday morning along the Intracoastal 
Waterway. 
</P>
<P>
	They never found the barge, but did see a swamped cabin cruiser  
and a swamped motorboat about 1 1/2 miles apart near Petit Bois 
Island, about 20 miles south of Pascagoula. 
</P>
</TEXT>
