<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ex-Speaker Wright Faces Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Former House Speaker Jim Wright faces  
surgery for oral cancer for a second time in nine years. 
</P>
<P>
	Wright, 76, will be operated on Friday at a Houston hospital to  
remove his cancerous right jawbone and reconstruct it with bone 
from one of his legs. 
</P>
<P>
	``I told them I didn't know whether I wanted to look like Clark  
Gable or John Wayne,'' Wright said. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1991, Wright lost part of his tongue and some teeth in his  
right jaw after a small, hard growth was found near the base of his 
tongue. He also underwent radiation treatment. 
</P>
<P>
	The Democrat left Congress in 1989 during an ethics  
investigation. The Ethics Committee concluded Wright had skirted 
ethics rules by making bulk sales of his book to unions and other 
groups. 
</P>
</TEXT>
