<P>
	Russians Withdrawn From Chechnya  
</P>
<P>
	GROZNY, Russia (AP) -- Russia ordered its government mission out  
of the breakaway republic of Chechnya today because of dangerous 
conditions, a news agency reported. The order to leave the republic 
came two days after a band of masked men kidnapped a top Kremlin 
official, dragging him from an airplane as it was about to leave 
the Chechen capital, Grozny, for Moscow. Russia and the rest of the 
world consider Chechnya a Russian province, but the territory runs 
its own affairs ever since the Chechens' 1994-96 war for 
independence from Moscow. 

</P>
