	Chinese Push for Sex Harassment Law  
</P>
<P>
	BEIJING (AP) -- Sexual harassment of women workers in China has  
become a ``very serious'' problem and legislators are taking action 
to prevent it, the China Youth Daily reported today. Thirty-two 
legislators submitted a proposal for a law against sexual 
harassment to the annual session of the Chinese legislature that 
opened Friday, the official newspaper said. The proposal submitted 
to the National People's Congress noted laws in other countries 
that bar sexual harassment, the newspaper said. 

</P>
<P>
	Directors Guild Honors Spielberg  
</P>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Steven Spielberg won the Directors Guild of  
America's award last night for ``Saving Private Ryan,'' making him 
and the epic World War II film strong favorites for Academy Awards. 
In winning a DGA award, Spielberg stands a strong chance of getting 
a director's award at the Oscars on March 21. Only four times has 
the DGA winner not repeated at the Academy Awards. The winner of 
the directing Oscar also usually sees his film take a best picture 
award. 

</P>
