Oregon State muddled the NCAA tournament seeding in the West by 
upsetting No. 6 Stanford 59-45 last night. Deaundra Tanner added 17 
points for the Beavers (13-14, 7-11 Pac-10) and outplayed Stanford 
guard Arthur Lee, who was held to just six points after scoring a 
combined 50 in his last two games. Stanford's point total was its 
season low, eclipsing a 57-49 loss to North Carolina in November. 

