<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Manistique Wins Santa Margarita </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- Manistique rebounded from a slow start to  
take the lead from pacesetter Magical Allure and win by three 
lengths Sunday in the $294,000 Santa Margarita Invitational 
Handicap. 
</P>
<P>
	Carrying a high weight of 122 pounds with Gary Stevens, the  
4-year-old filly passed Magical Allure on the far turn of the 
1 1/8-mile track and drew clear to finish first in a field of only 
four fillies and mares in 1:48 1/5. The win was Manistique's 
seventh in eight starts and first in a Grade I event. 
</P>
<P>
	India Divina finished third, one-half length behind Magical  
Allure, and Victory Stripes finished fourth. 
</P>
<P>
	Manistique, the 1-5 favorite, earned $180,000 to increase her  
career total to $646,700. 
</P>
<P>
	She returned $2.60 and $2.10. Magical Allure returned $2.20.  
</P>
</TEXT>
