<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Back Injury Cancels First Lady Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- A recurring back injury is keeping Hillary  
Rodham Clinton from accompanying the president on a four-day 
goodwill tour of Central America this week, the first lady's 
spokeswoman said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Clinton aggravated a previously injured back muscle while  
on a skiing vacation in Utah with her President Clinton and their 
daughter, Chelsea, said spokeswoman Marsha Berry. 
</P>
<P>
	The Clintons returned to the White House on March 1 after a few  
days in Park City, Utah, where Mrs. Clinton skied with Chelsea. 
</P>
<P>
	Berry said the first lady did not have enough time to recover  
properly before the trip beginning Monday to Nicaragua, El 
Salvador, Guatemala and Honduras, countries hardest hit by last 
fall's Hurricane Mitch. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Clinton toured the hurricane-struck area in November,  
shortly after Mitch hit. 
</P>
<P>
	She first hurt her back last spring.  
</P>
</TEXT>
