<HEADLINE> Quotes From Gov. Bush Announcement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AUSTIN, Texas (AP) -- Some quotes from Texas Gov. George W. Bush  
and some members of the presidential exploratory campaign committee 
he named Sunday: 

</P>
<P>
	``I want to tell my friends outside Texas, especially in the  
early primary states, I won't be able to visit until this summer.'' 
-- Bush. 

</P>
<P>
	``Laura and the girls and I have talked about this a great deal,  
and they have concluded that if I run, they just might vote for me. 
We have become comfortable that our love is strong enough to 
endure, that we are close enough, that our family will thrive no 
matter what life brings.'' -- Bush. 

</P>
<P>
	``When we get through with all of the exploring, the answer has  
got to be 'yes.''' -- George P. Schultz. 

</P>
<P>
	``We need to do all we can to encourage George W. and his lovely  
bride to make this decision.'' -- Rep. J.C. Watts, R-Okla. 

</P>
<P>
	``I hope that the Bush family will decide it's the right thing  
to do.'' -- Rep. Jennifer Dunn, R-Wash. 

</P>
<P>
	``I am confident this exploratory committee will find plenty of  
support for George Bush for president.'' -- Haley Barbour, former 
GOP chairman. 

</P>
<P>
	``A man who should become president, a man who I believe will  
become president.'' -- Michigan Gov. John Engler. 

</P>
<P>
	``We in Texas know you'll be every bit as impressed with him as  
we are.'' -- Rep. Henry Bonilla, R-Texas. 

</P>
<P>
	``There is tremendous enthusiasm all around America for you to  
be the best and next president of the United States.'' -- Rep. Roy 
Blunt, R-Mo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
