<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 20 Hurt in Colombia Stadium Mishap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) -- A railing in the second deck of a soccer  
stadium in Cali gave way Sunday, sending fans and the metal barrier 
crashing on spectators below. Twenty people were injured, three 
seriously, the Red Cross reported. 
</P>
<P>
	The railing at Pascual Guerrero Stadium loosened when jubilant  
America fans pressed against it after their team scored the game's 
first goal against Deportivo Cali. 
</P>
<P>
	In the resulting confusion, several America fans rushed the  
field and scuffled briefly with Cali's goalkeeper and a defender. 
The players were not injured, and play resumed 45 minutes after the 
accident. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1982, in a game between these same teams in this stadium, 22  
people were crushed in a stampede. The mayhem began when fans 
leaving the stadium were urinated on by spectators above them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
